The document [here|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BITBUCKET/pullrequests%2BResource#pullrequestsResource-Acceptandmergeapullrequest] says that the API for merging a pull request is https://bitbucket.org/api/2.0/repositories/{owner}/{repo_slug}/pullrequests/{pull_request_id}/merge.

However, this [comment|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BITBUCKET/Use%2Bthe%2BBitbucket%2BREST%2BAPIs%3FfocusedCommentId%3D420185137#comment-420185137] said the API is https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/user/slug/pullrequests/id/accept.

Notice the last parts of the two different urls.

In [REST API browser|http://restbrowser.bitbucket.org/], /merge is not even there, but /accept will return the following error:

{code}
#!json
{
  "error":  {
    "message": "Resource not found",
    "detail": "There is no API hosted at this URL.

For information about our API&#x27;s, please refer to the documentation at: https://confluence.atlassian.com/x/IYBGDQ"
  }
}
{code}

